review_blob: Tap at Beer Hunters, Pori. Opaque black color, small steady brownish head. Licorice, ash, dry aroma. Light-bodied to medium-bodied. Ashy, toasted flavor. Dry, not very fruity black ipa.

Bottle (Beer Hunters). Clear copper color, medium-sized creamy white head. Aroma has sweetish banana, Saison yeast but quite light pepperness. Light-bodied to medium-bodied. Flavor has banana-bubblegum, citric hoppyness. Fruity and sweet Saison with (too) clean palate. Feels too filtered.

Can (Beer Hunters). Amber color, good cloudy beige head, lace. Rye, citrus and caramel in the nose. Medium-bodied. Citrusy, ryeish, a bit spicey hoppyness with Caramalt base. As 5 months old same freshness issues but overall likeable.

Bottled 330ml (K-Supermarket City)
Dark amber color, small off-white head. Aroma has banana, riped berries and some kind of citrus-herbal hops. Light-bodied. Light wheaty banana maltyness, citrusy notes, caramalt, light yeasty notes. Overall very light with even watery finish. Summer terrace drink.

Bottled 330ml (K-Supermarket City)
Dark brown-ruby color, small beige head with some lace. Aroma has toasted malts, rye bread and yeast. Light-bodied. Toasted bready maltyness is similar to the stronger bocks. Clean malty palate with lingering sweetish malts and some hops. Of course would gain from the higher abv.

Bottled 330ml (K-Supermarket City)
Hazy orange color, small white head. Grassy aroma has light floral notes and some corn. Light-bodied. Harsh flavor with herbal, grassy hoppyness, underlying fruityness. Laitila house flavors. Long lingering herbal bitterness which is too harsh for my liking. Meh.

Bottle 330ml (Beer Hunters). Dark brown color, small steady beige head. Toffee, caramel, brown sugar and vanilla. Medium-bodied. Brown sugar, vanilla, bourbon. Grassy hoppyness. Sweet easy bourbon brew.

Can (1 pint, Beer Hunters). Amber color, good creamy white head. Riped fruits, citrus, grass and pineapple. Medium-bodied. Overriped fruits, citrus. Lingering citrus in the aftertaste. Feels not the freshiest.

Tap at Beer Hunters, Pori. Hazy orange color, small white head, lace. Funky fruity farmhouse aroma. Medium-bodied. Funky, fruity flavor with hoppy finish. Nice farmhouse ale. And yes, keg was checked.
Tap at Beer Hunters, Pori. Hazy yellow color, small white head. Grainy, orange peel, citrus aroma. Light-bodied. Light citrus, orange, orange peels and some grain. Easy fruity hoppy lager.
beer_name: BrewDog Prototype Session India Pale Lager (IPL)

review_blob:
Can 500ml (K-Supermarket City)
Hazy orange color, small white head. Tropical fruity riped mango aroma with hints of resin. Light-bodied. Fruity, pale malty, Some citrusy and yeasty notes in the finish. Ok APA although it is not so interesting as their IPA.

Can (ABM)
Bright red color, small white head. Milky, cherry, tartish but also a bit candyish aroma. Light-bodied. Tartish, milky blackberry flavor. Simple but somewhat pleasant in its genre,
beer_name: Black Market Tradecraft Series: Blackberry Sour

review_blob:
Can (AbM, canned 17.07.2015)
Slightly hazy amber color, small white head. Fruity orange jam, mango aroma. Light-bodied. Pale malty, tropical fruity flavor (mango, pineapple and citrus). Easy pale ale, goes with food. Some bready notes as it is not very fresh can.

Bottled 500ml (Alko)
Hazy amber-copper color, small off-white head. Aroma has fruityness, resin and notes of alcohol. Medium-bodied. Fruity flavor with some banana. Then resin, pine and even hints of salty licorice. Some warming alcohol in the lingering, hoppy aftertaste. Smooth, balanced double ipa with the alcohol rush.

Can 330ml (AbM)
Deep amber color, good cloudy beige head - can was a kind of gusher (wet shorts now!). Aroma has pineapple, citrus and mango. Light-bodied. Flavor has grapefruity, grass, citrus and tropical fruits. Some harshness in the middle of juicy hoppyness. Nice sweet-fruity session ipa anyhow.

Bottled 330ml (K-Kamppi, batch 130, BB 12/2017!)
Hazy orange color, small white head. Grassy, grainy aroma. Light-bodied. Very grainy flavor, harsh, light fruityness, watery finish. I wonder where all Amarillo and Centennial have gone? Already now feels boring, what about in December 2017?

Bottled 500ml (K-Kamppi)
Opaque black color, small brownish head. Sweetish lactose-licorice aroma, toasted maltyness. Light-bodied. Lactose milky, licorice, some tobacco in the flavor. Smooth although light, needs ABV. Well brewed (its from Malmgrd so I am not suprised).

Bottled 500ml (K-Kamppi)
Hazy orange color, small white head. Grassy, hop pellet sack aroma. Light-bodied. Grassy, harsh "raw hop pellety" hoppyness. Long aftertaste. Suprisingly harsh for having even some wheat. Tastes more like rye ipa gone wrong as it taste similar to Saimaan Joker Hop Ale.
Bottle 750ml (Vinmonopolet). Hazy orange color, good creamy off-white head. Spicey, dry yeasty aroma. Medium-bodied. Fruity, spicey, dry yeasty flavor. Fruity, a bit messy.

Bottle 330ml (Arkadia). Murky orange-yellow color, good cloudy off-white head. Aroma has ginger/coriander spiceyness, some fruity notes. Medium-bodied. Riped fruits, ginger, coriander, yeast. Messy spicey triple.
beer_name: Abbazia Tre Fontane Tripel Birra Trappista Italiana

review_blob: Bottle (from FL). Dark brown color, small off-white head. Aroma has artifical chocolate, cardboardish malts, espresso. Light-bodied. Sweet chocolate, cocoa, vanilla, harsh. Njet.

Bottle 330ml (Vinmonopolet). Dark ruby color, small off-white head. Tartish fruity Rodenbach-like aroma with riped fruits. Light-bodied to medium-bodied. Riped fruits, date, tartness. Short sweetish finish. Mellow but very easy.
UPDATED: APR 23, 2016
beer_name: Ngne  / Mikkeller / Brewdog Horizon Tokyo Black

review_blob: Can (from FL). Hazy orange color, small steady white head, good lacing. Sweet mango, orange fruity aroma. Medium-bodied. Pineapple, mango, grapefruit in the fruity flavor. High drinkable, tasty apa.
Bottle 330ml (Petalax). Clear amber color, small white head. Caramel, grainy aroma. Light-bodied. Caramel, harsh grassy hops. Even alcohol. Industrial.
Bottle 330ml (Vinmonopolet). Opaque brown color, medium-sized brownish head. Aroma is toasted, woody and slightly tart. Medium-bodied. Toasted, tartish, spicey flavor. Alcoholic punch. Restless.

Bottle (from SuperAlko). Dark ruby-brown color, small beige head. Strong nose has artifical coffee and chocolate. Medium-bodied. Sweetish artifical flavor has more chocolate than coffee. Toasted malty. Meeh.
Bottle (Vinmonopolet). Deep ruby color, small steady beige head. Bready, malty aroma. Medium-bodied. Bready, malty, sweetish. Good German style bock. Hides ABV well.
UPDATED: APR 23, 2016
Bottle 500ml (Vinmonopolet). Dark ruby, brown color, small brownish head. Rye bready, caramel in the nose. Medium-bodied. Ryeish, a bit burned malty flavor. Too bready for my liking.
Bottle (from Uba ja Humal). Dark opaque brown color, good beige head. Aroma has smoke, wood, dark malts and licorice. Medium-bodied. Ash, toasted malty, fruity hoppyness, dryish finish. Ok.
Bottle (Vinmonopolet). Dark ruby color, big cloudy beige head. Berryish, malty aroma. Dull. Medium-bodied. Caramel, some chocolate, alcohol, grassy earthy hops. Active carbonation. Meh
Bottle (Petalax). Golden color, small white head. Musty, a bit fruity grainy aroma. Light-bodied. Harsh, grainy, light sweetish bulk lager. Short finish. Crap.
Bottle (Petalax). Hazy orange color, small steady white head. Aroma has orange jam. Medium-bodied. Honeyish, riped fruits in the flavor. Quite full taste for 4.4% beer.
UPDATED: APR 23, 2016
Bottle 330ml (Petalax). Clear golden color, small white head. Sweetish malty, grainy aroma. Light-bodied. Sweetish malty, harsh, grassy supermarket lager. Ok in its category.
Bottle from SuperAlko. Dark brown color, medium-sized brown head. Toasted malty, blueberry aroma. Medium-bodied. Toasted, blueberries, ginger in the flavor. Nice robust stout. Better than expected.

Bottle (Petalax). Deep amber color, steady off-white head. Fruity, woody, dry yeasty aroma. Medium-bodied. Orange jam, citrus, pine in the sweet and hoppy flavor. Quite typical yeasty ned/bel area ipa.
Bottle 500ml (Vinmonopolet). Amber-copper color, small white head. Tartish, cranberryish aroma. Light-bodied. Tartish, riped coffee, fot the nose

Bottle 330ml (Vinmonopolet). Clear deep amber color, small beige head. Light grassy, sweetish caramel aroma. Light-bodied to medium-bodied. Watery front. A bit sweetish with toffee, grassy hops. Lingering bitterness. Simplish.
Bottle (Petalax). Hazy orange color, small white head. Honeyish, riped fruits in the nose. Light-bodied. Honey, grass and grain. Light, sweetish and bland.

Bottle 330ml. Slightly hazy yellow color, small white head. Riped fruits, apricot in the nose, sweetish. Light-bodied to medium-bodied. Sparkling. Honeyish, sweetish pale malty, a bit papery flavor. Very typical blonde.
Bottle from SuperAlko. Dark amber color, small off-white head. Caramel, toffee sweetness in the nose. Medium-bodied. Caramel-toffee flavor, alcohol. No substance.
UPDATED: APR 22, 2016
Bottle 500ml (Vinmonopolet). Dark ruby color, good creamy beige head. Berryish, malty, caramel aroma. Medium-bodied. Hopy, somewhat alcoholic, malty. Powerful American Strong Ale.

Bottle 500ml (Vinmonopolet). Opaque brown color, steady medium-sized beige head. Bread and caramel, very close to some East European baltic porters. Medium-bodied. Caramel, some berryish notes, toasted maltyness. Sweetish. Reminds me about Aldaris Porteris.
beer_name: Ngne  Gottes Hlfe in der Noth

review_blob: Bottle 500ml (Petalax). Dark ruby color, small beige head. Caramel, yeast, some chocolate in the nose. Light-bodied to medium-bodied. Flavor has spices, caramel and roasted malts. Feels more like a stout than brown ale.

Bottle 330ml (Petalax). Dark ruby color, small beige head. Caramel, light berries and spices in the nose. Medium-bodied. Caramel, some toasted notes, grass and spices. Quite typical Norwegian xmas beer.
UPDATED: APR 22, 2016

Bottle (Vinmonopolet). Dark brown color, small beige head. Caramel, red wine, berries and some alcohol. Complex. Medium-bodied to full-bodied. Toffeeish, wineous, some alcohol. Nice complex quadrupel.
